{"lemma": "تاجِرٌ", "slug": "تاجِرٌ", "root": "ت.ج.ر", "root_slug": "ت-ج-ر", "root_link": "/words/roots/ت-ج-ر", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": true, "lemma_key": "تاجِرٌ", "root": "أجر", "pos": "V", "occurrence_count": 1}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 1, "pos_tags": ["verb"], "has_etymology": false, "sense_count": 0}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n3783"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AA%D8%A7%D8%AC%D9%90%D8%B1%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "merchant", "fa": "تاجر", "ur": "تاجر", "tr": "tüccar", "id": "pedagang", "bn": "ব্যপারী", "es": "comerciante", "fr": "marchand", "de": "Händler", "ru": "торговец", "zh": "商人"}, "definition": null, "etymology": null, "ipa": null, "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n3783", "headword_ar": "تَاجِرٌ", "root": "tjr", "body": [{"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A merchant; one who practises traffic, merchandise,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "commerce; a trafficker; a trader,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "tradesman; a dealer; one who sells and buys;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "one who sells and buys for gain:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Ksh in ii. 15:) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a vintner,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "seller of wine,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K,) was also called thus by the Arabs: (S:) accord. to IAth, this latter is said to be the primary signification: and hence the saying in a trad.,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_in~a", "text_ar": "اـِنَّ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alt~aAjira faAjirN", "text_ar": "التَّاجِرَ فَاجِرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Verily the vintner is a transgressor"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (TA:) pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_